{
  "texts": [
    "For example, Lin et al. [228] proposed a unified multidimensional automated evaluation approach, LLM-EVAL, for domain conversations.",
    "PandaLM [229] trained an additional LLM to evaluate different models, which is suitable for reproducible and automated language model evaluation.Human Evaluation: Human evaluation aims to assess the quality and accuracy of FM-generated results by human participation.",
    "Different from automated evaluation, human evaluation focuses more on specific application scenarios and can provide more comprehensive results.",
    "Usually, evaluators consist of experts, researchers or the target users.",
    "Recent human evaluation methods involve tasks including generation, summarization and analogical reasoning tasks."
  ]
}